In the predominant media retelling of this pandemic’s history, public health officials such as Dr. Anthony Fauci sounded the alarm from day one, warning the public of everything that has come to pass.
Even as the virus reached the United States, U.S. and international public health officials continued to downplay its severity and risk.
English language news coverage monitored by the GDELT Project shows that locations mentioned in global coverage of the virus grew in three stages.
Had politicians and public health officials sounded the alarm from the beginning and maintained consistent messaging of the virus’ domestic threat, perhaps the public would be more accepting of quarantine and economic disruption.
With the press sounding this latest theme, public health officials’ desire to continue lockdowns indefinitely is running head-on into increased awareness of this action’s incalculable economic and emotional toll.